-- Iran to Allocate $11 Billion to Ministries With Debts, IRNA Says
-- B y   L a d a n e   N a s s e r i
-- 2012-03-27T12:15:41Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-03-27/iran-to-allocate-11-billion-to-ministries-with-debts-irna-says.html
Iran ’s government allocated 135
trillion rials ($11 billion) to four ministries to clear debts
to contractors, the official  Islamic Republic News Agency 
reported, citing the government’s information office.  Some 60 trillion rials will be given to the Oil Ministry,
40 trillion to the Energy Ministry, 35 trillion to the Justice
Ministry and about 3 billion to the  Interior Ministry , IRNA said
without giving details of projects for which the ministries are
in debt or a timeline for the payments.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Ladane Nasseri in Dubai at 
 lnasseri@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Andrew J. Barden at 
 barden@bloomberg.net  